<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-05-25T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-05-25T12:00:00-05:00" n="320" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d320">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB Palestine/5–2548: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Consulate General</gloss> at Jerusalem</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-05-25T13:00:00-04:00">May 25,
                                    1948—1 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>467. Burdett authorized informally to represent this govt on <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> Truce Commission pending appointment by
                            the President of official representative replacing Wasson.<note n="1" xml:id="d320fn1">Consul Wasson, on his return to the Consulate
                                General at Jerusalem from a meeting of the Security Council Truce
                                Commission on May 22, was fatally wounded by a sniper’s bullet and
                                died the next day; for Ambassador Austin’s report of May 22 on the
                                matter, see <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>, <hi rend="italic">3rd
                                    yr., Supplement for May 1948</hi>, p. 94.</note> Repeated to
                                <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> as 321, Paris as 1787,
                            Brussels as 779, London as 1898. Jerusalem repeat to Arab capitals.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>